The paper deals with a statistical model for group testing, which involves binary random variables and a priori probabilities of being defective. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. Additionally, the paper proposes algorithms for identifying the subset of defectives, which involves non-linear binary measurements, indicating a possible connection to the Data Structures (cs.DS) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the information-theoretic lower bound and provides simulations, which are relevant to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories.
